<div class="problem"><p><a class="knowl" acro="D" type="Proof Technique" title="Definitions" knowl="./knowls/technique.D.knowl">Proof Technique D</a> asks you to formulate a definition of what it means for a whole number to be odd.  What is your definition?  (Do not say “the opposite of even.”)  Is $6$ odd?  Is $11$ odd?  Justify your answers by using your definition.
</p></div>
